  "key_relationships": [
    "ServiceManager creates/caches Service instances (HashMap<ServiceFixedConfig, Weak<Service>>)",
    "Service owns UpdateableWafInstance (composition)",
    "Service owns ConfigSnapshot via ArcSwap (atomic swap on RC update)",
    "Service owns ServiceFixedConfig (immutable, used as cache key)",
    "UpdateableWafInstance wraps libddwaf::Handle (Arc<Handle> via ArcSwap) and libddwaf::Builder (Mutex)",
    "Client holds &'static ServiceManager and Option<TrackedService>",
    "TrackedService wraps Arc<Service> with RAII worker count tracking",
    "Command/CommandResponse are protocol DTOs carried over dd_conn (C) / UnixStream (Rust)",
    "ClientInitArgs contains WafSettings + RemoteConfigSettings + TelemetrySettings + SidecarSettings",
    "RequestInitArgs/RequestExecArgs/RequestShutdownArgs carry WafMap data to WAF",
    "ActionInstance is returned in all Resp types to signal blocking/redirect actions",
    "req_info_init embeds req_info (composition), req_info embeds block_params",
    "dd_command_spec uses function pointers for outgoing_cb/incoming_cb (strategy pattern)",
    "HelperManager manages dd_conn lifecycle; acquired conn is used by all command functions",
    "RequestLifecycle calls RequestAbort on dd_should_block/dd_should_redirect results",
    "WafRuleset converts to libddwaf::WafObject via From trait",
    "RcUpdateState holds ConfigPoller + AsmFeatureConfigManager + TelemetryMetricsCollector"
  ],

  "key_flows": [
    "Request init: PHP rinit -> dd_req_lifecycle_rinit -> dd_helper_mgr_acquire_conn -> dd_request_init(conn, req_info_init) -> helper runs WAF -> returns actions/triggers -> if dd_should_block, dd_req_lifecycle_abort -> dd_request_abort_static_page/redirect",
    "Request exec (RASP): PHP hook -> dd_request_exec(conn, data, req_exec_opts{rasp_rule}, block_params) -> helper runs WAF with rasp context -> returns block verdict",
    "Request shutdown: rshutdown -> dd_request_shutdown -> helper finalizes WAF context -> returns schema/metrics",
    "RC update: sidecar notifies -> ServiceManager.notify_of_rc_updates -> Service.poll_and_apply_rc -> apply_config -> waf.add_or_update_config / waf.update -> config_snapshot updated atomically",
    "WAF update cycle: add_or_update_config (locks builder, no rebuild) -> update() (rebuilds Handle, ArcSwap store) -> current() (lock-free load of Arc<Handle>)",
    "Client lifecycle: Server accepts UnixStream -> Client::new -> entrypoint -> client_init command -> get/create Service -> request_init/exec/shutdown loop -> disconnect"
  ],

  "important_notes": [
    "Protocol: msgpack tuples [command_name, [args...]], framed with 'dds\\0' header + uint32 little-endian size, max 4MB",
    "WAF thread safety: ArcSwap<Handle> for lock-free concurrent reads; Mutex<Builder> for serialized config updates",
    "Initial ruleset is auto-restored when all ASM_DD remote configs are removed",
    "RC products handled: ASM_DD (rules), ASM (customizations), ASM_DATA (IP lists), ASM_FEATURES (enable/disable)",
    "RASP support: req_exec_opts.rasp_rule identifies RASP rule, WafRunType::RaspRule in Rust protocol",
    "Blocking: dd_should_block -> response_type_auto/html/json with response_code 403 or redirect 303",
    "Schema extraction: sampled by SchemaSampler, controlled by WafSettings.schema_extraction",
    "AutoUserInstrumMode controls automated user identification/anonymization mode from ASM_FEATURES",
    "helper_runtime enum tracks whether C++ or Rust helper is running",
    "TrackedService RAII increments/decrements worker_count for metrics"
  ],

